def_cn: (得分相同时的)加赛，决胜赛;(得票相同时的)决胜投票，决胜选举
def_en: A run-off is an extra vote or contest which is held in order to decide the winner of an election or competition, because no-one has yet clearly won.

def_cn: 径流，溢流（指流入河流中的雨水）
def_en: Run-off is rainwater that forms a stream rather than being absorbed by the ground.
